records.addlTxt:
Defendant Darryl Bernard Gooden in court with attorney Anne A. Devitt.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.   

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Toylibra G.
The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 5 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 1/2 years with credit for 6 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2 1/2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of 3 years
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 -  The Court ordered the defendant to serve 10 months, in the House of Correction, with release to the Day Reporting Center to include parenting classes and         work. Good time allowed.  The report date is stayed until May 27, 2015 by 5:00 pm.  
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Obtain G.E.D;
 - Participate in a parenting program;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Provide DNA sample;
 - No Contact with Co-Actors: Pekory Terrell, Tramaine Reed, Ashley or Brittany;
 - Restitution is set at zero;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge plus costs, surcharges and disbursements. Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would then be paid while on extended supervison.   Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Sentencing Referral Form;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
